cator\n- Packet buffers\n\n**Utilities** (`src/util/`):\n- Hash maps\n- Ring buffers\n- Priority queues\n- Intrusive lists\n- Varint encoding\n- CRC32C checksums\n\n#### **3. Public API** (`include/nxp/`)\n\n**Connection Management**:\n```c\nnxp_result nxp_connect(config, host, port, callbacks, ...);\nvoid nxp_conn_close(conn, error_code);\nnxp_conn_state nxp_conn_get_state(conn);\n```\n\n**Server Listener**:\n```c\nnxp_result nxp_listen(config, bind_addr, port, on_new_conn, ...);\nvoid nxp_listener_close(listener);\n```\n\n**Stream Operations**:\n```c\nnxp_result nxp_stream_open(conn, type, priority, callbacks, ...);\nssize_t nxp_stream_send(stream, data, len, fin);\nssize_t nxp_stream_recv(stream, buf, len, &fin);\nvoid nxp_stream_close(stream);\n```\n\n**Event Loop**:\n```c\nnxp_result nxp_init(config);\nvoid nxp_run();      // Blocking\nvoid nxp_poll();     // Non-blocking\nvoid nxp_shutdown();\n```\n\n#### **4. Stream Types**\n- **RELIABLE**: Ordered, reliable (TCP-like)\n- **FAST**: Unordered, unreliable (UDP-like)\n- **MEDIA**: Partially reliable (drop old data)\n- **FILE**: Bulk transfer optimized\n\n#### **5. Advanced Features**\n\n**Built-in Capabilities**:\n- ✅ Heartbeat/keep-alive\n- ✅ Connection migration (IP address changes)\n- ✅ 0-RTT reconnection\n- ✅ Per-stream rate limiting\n- ✅ Backpressure callbacks\n- ✅ Session resumption\n- ✅ Stateless retry (DDoS protection)\n\n**Congestion Control**:\n- BBR algorithm with delivery rate tracking\n- Adaptive pacing based on bandwidth estimation\n- Network-type detection\n\n**Security**:\n- Mandatory encryption (no plaintext mode)\n- Perfect Forward Secrecy\n- Replay protection\n- Token-based authentication\n- Proof-of-work for handshake (optional)\n\n#### **6. Project Structure**\n\n```\nNXP/\n├── include/nxp/          # Public API headers\n├── src/\n│   ├── api/              # Public API implementation\n│   ├── core/             # Protocol engine\n│   ├── congestion/       # BBR, pacing, delivery rate\n│   ├──